A class is a blueprint
    means it has all the structure (like suppose you have to build a house then first we need to create a blueprint for it like for example xyz should be the dimension of the kitchen , there should be 4 room of abc measurment and many more) so lets call them variables and the funcitons.

    And when we build the house or the blueprint structure in real. then it is called a assigning object
A Object is a instance of the class. (means real presence of the blueprint, like all the values or the methods(function) is initialised.

class take 1byte size
